WEBVTT

00:00:00.111 --> 00:00:00.852
Precision Point.

00:00:01.452 --> 00:00:03.033
Trust is not an emotional state.

00:00:03.473 --> 00:00:06.715
It is a calculated risk assessment based on predictable congruence.

00:00:07.436 --> 00:00:14.520
Interpersonal trust encompasses one's willingness to accept vulnerability based on the expectation regarding the behavior of another party.

00:00:15.221 --> 00:00:21.344
It is built on four distinct pillars, sincerity, reliability, competence, and care.

00:00:22.345 --> 00:00:24.266
Consider this structured contrasting case.

00:00:25.006 --> 00:00:31.670
Leader A relies on positional authority to enforce compliance, dictating tasks without explaining the underlying logic.

00:00:32.510 --> 00:00:41.095
Leader B relies on value congruence, transparently mapping their decisions to shared organizational values and demonstrating the four pillars of trust.

00:00:42.016 --> 00:00:47.959
Identify which strategy succeeds in a complex matrix environment and justify your reasoning before proceeding.

00:00:48.742 --> 00:00:53.235
Leader B succeeds because positional authority cannot scale across boundary-less networks.

00:00:53.897 --> 00:01:01.960
Only a positive risk assessment, generated by predictable congruence, allows for the decentralized execution required in modern enterprises.
